Ruby programmer? It’s easy to use this data in your own app! Use the gem like this: 

require 'everypolitician'
country = Everypolitician::Index.new.country('Portugal')
house = country.legislature('Assembly')
house.popolo.terms.find_by(id: 'term/11').memberships.each do |membership|
  puts "#{membership.person.name} (#{membership.party.name}): #{membership.person.gender}"
end

Libraries also available in Python and PHP.

Main Sources: https://github.com/centraldedados/parlamento-deputados, http://demo.cratica.org/, http://wikidata.org/, http://gender-balance.org/

Anything wrong? If you've spotted an error, or the data is incomplete, here's how to get that fixed.

EveryPolitician

A simple but ambitious project to collect and share data about every politician in every country in the world, in a consistent, open format that anyone can use.
